<MAN>
<LANGUAGE>eng</LANGUAGE>
<TITLE>mat2gray</TITLE>
<TYPE>SIVP Toolbox</TYPE>
<DATE>April, 2006</DATE>
<SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="mat2gray">Convert matrix to grayscale image</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
<CALLING_SEQUENCE>
   <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>G = mat2gray(M)</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
   <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>G = mat2gray(M, [mmin, mmax])</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
</CALLING_SEQUENCE>
<PARAM>
<PARAM_INDENT>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>M</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     An matrix/image.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>[mmin, mmax]</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     <TT>[mmin, mmax]</TT> is the values in <TT>M</TT> that correspond to <TT>0.0</TT> and <TT>1.0</TT> in <TT>G</TT>. The elements in <TT>M</TT> which is lower than <TT>mmin</TT> will be converted to <TT>0.0</TT>, and greater than <TT>mmax</TT> will be converted to <TT>1.0</TT>.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>G</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
     A double precision matrix/image which data value in the range [0,1].
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
</PARAM_INDENT>
</PARAM>
<DESCRIPTION>
<P>
<TT>mat2gray(M,[mmin, mmax])</TT> converts the matrix <TT>M</TT> to the double precision image. 
The output matrix contains values in the range <TT>[0.0, 1.0]</TT>. 
<TT>mmin</TT> and <TT>mmax</TT> are the values in <TT>M</TT> that correspond to 0.0 and 1.0 in the output image.
</P>
<P>
When <TT>[mmin, mmax]</TT> is not specified, <TT>minimum</TT> and <TT>maximum</TT> of <TT>M</TT> are the values in <TT>M</TT> that correspond to 0.0 and 1.0 in the output image.
</P>

</DESCRIPTION>
<EXAMPLE><![CDATA[

    M = [0:10;0:10];
    I = mat2gray(im);

]]></EXAMPLE>

